  "prompt": "What are some animals native to New Zealand?",
  "response": "New Zealand has several unique native animals, including:\n\n1. Kiwi (bird)\n- National bird of New Zealand\n- Flightless bird with a long beak\n- Several species exist\n\n2. Tuatara\n- Ancient reptile species\n- Often called a \"living fossil\"\n- Looks like a lizard but is not a lizard\n\n3. Kakapo\n- Large, flightless parrot\n- Critically endangered\n- World's only flightless parrot species\n\n4. Kea\n- Alpine parrot\n- Known for being very intelligent\n- Only alpine parrot in the world\n\n5. New Zealand Fur Seal\n- Marine mammal native to New Zealand's coastlines\n\n6. Morepork (native owl)\n- Small nocturnal owl\n- Named after its distinctive call\n\n7. Short-tailed Bat\n- One of only two native mammal species in New Zealand\n- Endemic to the country\n\n8. Weta\n- Large insect species\n- Some are quite large and unique to New Zealand\n\nMost of these animals are found nowhere else in the world and have evolved in isolation, making them particularly special to New Zealand's ecosystem.",
